Had a pumpkin chai muffin which was yummy...but not sure if there was more to be had...lol. the Coffee was good but to be honest the back garden made the entire experience. Highly recommended as a  meetup destination with friends, a place to sit with your thoughts and with free Wifi..
A place to work quietly. Definitely would recommend and visit again.

I have been going to Rosie’s for the last few years as a Charlotte native, and have always had a pleasant experience. This weekend I hosted a bridal shower which was had 13 attendees. It was a busy day for gatherings there, and overall the event went well.

I had a very unfortunate interaction with the owner, that I personally felt could have been handled in a more professional manner. I had moved a small table to our area where our shower was happening. The owner approached me and asked for me to not do so, and I felt as though I was very apologetic and was happy to put the table back (I was not fully aware at the time of the not moving furniture request). I’m just disappointed because I felt as though him and I could have had a calm, private conversation about this, but it felt very public and reprimanding towards me. I truly love going to Rosie’s and did not have any intention of being not mindful about seating for others, but his words were stern and harsh towards a customer who was not only overly understanding and apologetic, but also purchased over $200 of wine by the end of the event.

To end on a positive note since I really do love Rosie’s and I hate to even write this review, the other staff were so accommodating and helpful. They provided great knowledge in wine selection, provided wine buckets to keep the white wines chilled, and just were overall super considerate to anything we needed. My two star review is purely a reflection of how the owner communicated with me.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Olivia, 
Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback regarding your recent experience at Rosie’s. We genuinely appreciate your support and your kind words about our staff.

We apologize for the interaction you had with our owner during your event. Our policy regarding the movement of tables and chairs is in place to ensure a comfortable atmosphere for all our guests. We understand that you may not have been fully aware of this policy, and we appreciate your willingness to cooperate. Moving forward, please keep in mind of this policy and ask a staff member to help you. 

While we strive to maintain a welcoming environment, we must also prioritize the experience of all our patrons. Our intention is never to reprimand but to maintain the integrity of our space.

We're glad to hear that the rest of your experience was positive, and we hope you'll continue to enjoy Rosie’s in the future. Thank you once again for your understanding.

I had moved a small table to our area where our shower was happening. The owner approached me and asked for me to not do so, and I felt as though I was very apologetic and was happy to put the table back (I was not fully aware at the time of the not moving furniture request). I’m just disappointed because I felt as though him and I could have had a calm, private conversation about this, but it felt very public and reprimanding towards me. I truly love going to Rosie’s and did not have any intention of being not mindful about seating for others, but his words were stern and harsh towards a customer who was not only overly understanding and apologetic, but also purchased over $200 of wine by the end of the event.

To end on a positive note since I really do love Rosie’s and I hate to even write this review, the other staff were so accommodating and helpful. They provided great knowledge in wine selection, provided wine buckets to keep the white wines chilled, and just were overall super considerate to anything we needed. reviews_data.owner_answer:
Olivia, 
Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback regarding your recent experience at Rosie’s. We genuinely appreciate your support and your kind words about our staff.

We apologize for the interaction you had with our owner during your event. Our policy regarding the movement of tables and chairs is in place to ensure a comfortable atmosphere for all our guests. We understand that you may not have been fully aware of this policy, and we appreciate your willingness to cooperate. Moving forward, please keep in mind of this policy and ask a staff member to help you. 

While we strive to maintain a welcoming environment, we must also prioritize the experience of all our patrons. Our intention is never to reprimand but to maintain the integrity of our space.

We're glad to hear that the rest of your experience was positive, and we hope you'll continue to enjoy Rosie’s in the future. Thank you once again for your understanding.

reviews_data.review_text: Gorgeous garden with plenty of outdoor space for larger groups and smaller tables for couples.  You can grab a glass of wine, beer or a coffee but they’ve also got plenty of wine by the bottle options as well.  They typically have heaters in the winter so it’s even a great place on a cooler evening.  It is a fun place to explore and the laid back vibe makes it a great space for dates or catching up with friends.
Hidden Gem. Gorgeous gardens with a very relaxing feel. I could have stayed for hours.
Beautiful! Good wine and good times
Beautiful outdoor seating and fun trivia night

Stumbled upon this place one late Friday night. Possibly the most ethereal, magical place I’ve ever been to!! Good selection of wines. I want to come back for their coffee sometime. The staff was super cool too. Lots of seating options outside, good music, great vibes. The garden at night was so beautiful, like a pretty summer garden party. 12/10 🪄
Awesome place, beautiful garden area with plenty of plants and cool seating areas! The coffee is pretty good as well!
Their coffee is OK. The garden is lovely with plenty of room to social distance.

We had our first visit here today. This spot has a cool vibe. My wife and i chose the Vinabade Albariño, a delightful Spanish white wine with deep stone fruit aromas, and just the right acidity. We enjoyed our wine in a beautiful garden setting. This spot is a must for your wine experience in NODA. They offer an affordable, yet dynamic wine list, filled with all kinds of goodies! Thank you Dan and staff for a 5 star experience. We will be back! ✌️❤️🍷
Great place to sip wine! Very eclectic selection by the glass and a huge shady garden to sit and sip. Staff is very knowledgeable and friendly.
Beautiful garden. Nice selection of wines. Good coffee. I'll definitely be back.
